description: Gold Springs Resource Corp. engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties in the United States. The company primarily explores for gold and silver deposits. It holds a 100% interest in the Gold Springs gold-silver project covering approximately 7,800 hectares located in eastern Lincoln County, Nevada, and western Iron County, Utah. The company was formerly known as TriMetals Mining Inc. and changed its name to Gold Springs Resource Corp. in November 2019. Gold Springs Resource Corp. was incorporated in 2006 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
